ves, the great emphasis is given to the elaboration process and the description of the virtual game as a virtual physics learning object and analysis of a pilot tests conducted with undergraduate students in physics. Early tests show how the educational material developed can be analyzed from the perspective of previously concepts construction, especially with regard to the clarification and possible subsumers facilitate conceptual links.},
   author = {Fernando Custodio and Cerqueira Campos and João Ricardo and Neves Da Silva},
   issn = {2359-6082},
